raw_data.title: Quality Control/Trainer
raw_data.description: Evaluates, tests, and/or validates product services. Analyzes deficiencies in service or performance and recommends and/or implements improvements to address problems. Designs and implements quality control, error reduction and remediation programs. Ensures that project/department milestones/goals are met and adhering to quality standards. Extensive knowledge of department processes as well as industry and governmental quality regulations. Audits and reviews quality data according to existing documents and procedures. Contributes to moderately complex aspects of a project. Delivers company training programs and workshops to employees and managers. Monitors the effectiveness of training on employees using individual or group performance results. Collects feedback on sessions from attendees to use for future improvements to content and presentation. Contributes to new training program design and existing program enhancements. Develops and creates lesson plans and training aids. May specialize in a particular technical subject matter area, training program, or function of the company. Training programs may typically include topics such as supervisory/management training, research/work skills training, team building, and communications.
